# Copy this file to ".env" and paste your real keys after the "=".
# Never commit the real .env — it is git-ignored for you.
#
# Magpie's DEFAULT brain (Claude on your Claude Code subscription) needs NO key —
# and the ENGINE makes no LLM call at all (sourcing is deterministic). So the
# out-of-the-box setup needs NOTHING in this file.

# --- LLM brain (chat REPL + memory distiller only) ---------------------------
# DEFAULT (MAGPIE_LLM unset) = Claude on your Claude Code SUBSCRIPTION via the Agent
# SDK. No key required. Do NOT set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — it is NOT needed for the
# default, and if set it makes the SDK bill the pay-per-token API instead of your
# subscription (llm.py warns you if it sees it).
#
# Switch brains with the MAGPIE_LLM env var (one switch, see llm.py):
#   MAGPIE_LLM=gemini    -> needs GEMINI_API_KEY below
#   MAGPIE_LLM=deepseek  -> needs DEEPSEEK_API_KEY below

# Google Gemini (free) — only for MAGPIE_LLM=gemini (and the weak-model persona test).
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-free-gemini-api-key-here

# DeepSeek — only for MAGPIE_LLM=deepseek.
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your-deepseek-api-key-here

# --- Source-API keys (ALL optional + free; a missing key skips that source) --
# Most of Magpie's allowlist is keyless (Openverse, Wikimedia, The Met, Library of
# Congress, Internet Archive, NASA). These three are the only ones that need a free
# key, and Magpie silently skips any whose key is absent — it never blocks a run.
# SMITHSONIAN_API_KEY=your-free-data.gov-key
# PEXELS_API_KEY=your-free-pexels-key
# PIXABAY_API_KEY=your-free-pixabay-key
